\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Was anything ever made of a birthday in your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Oh yes. Everyone had their birthday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Did you get presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Oh yes, small presents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Did you get anything special to eat? Did you get a dumpling that day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Oh, I can\rquote t remember these things. It - it wasn\rquote 
t so important as all that. I remember - being asked what I wanted for my birthday, and I said - I wanted Burns\rquote s poems. Well - the little book, Burns\rquote s poems that I got, it\rquote s in the house yet but of course - the wages wouldn\rquote 
t stretch to what I wanted. I wanted the whole - Burns\rquote s - volumes, well - my sister remembered that and when I was twenty-one she bought me three volumes of Burns\rquote 
s poems, and I never rested until I had them devoured. Because I think - Burns had all the words of the dictionary at his fingertips and he could martial them at will. And there\rquote s some of the loveliest passages in his poems that you ever heard. Suc
h as that one - in Tam-o\rquote shanta. Pleasures all like poppies, spread, you seixe the flowr, it\rquote s bloom is shed. Or like the snow falls on the river, a moment white then emlts forever. Now there\rquote s - there\rquote s -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Did you feel being on the land as you were tha
t you were quite close to Burns as a poet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 I don\rquote t know but - Burns has always been a favourite - of mine.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 How old would you be when you got that book of poems then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Well - I was quite small when I got the little small book, but - it was o
nly small poems that was in it, it wasn\rquote t the - whole thing. The volumes that my sister bought me - I don\rquote t know whether there\rquote s - it\rquote s the whole - the whole of Burns\rquote s - poems, and she - she\rquote 
d heard - she had remembered - that I wanted Burns\rquote s poems and she bought me these for my twenty-first birthday.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 How about Christmas, can you tell me what Christmas was like in hour house?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 
Well, Christmas we all - always had a Christmas tree at the school that we were at, there was people - the name of Crabbe in Duncow, Colonel Crabbes just died a few years ago that was Lord }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13318710\charrsid12015019 Lieutenant}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 
 of the country, well he was their son. He was the son. His father and mother always gave the schoolchildren at Duncow schools a Christmas tree, and we always got a present off this tree.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Did you get the present from the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 
No, they had the Christmas tree, one of the trees cut down and put up in the school, and - the two - daughters - Major Crabbe was the father, Major Crabbe\rquote s two daughters and they all - decora
ted this tree, and - we were all invited, all the children from the school and your name was called out, and you went up and - one of the daughters presented you with whatever you were to get, I can remember getting a - a splendid knife. Oh that - that su
ited me up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 What about in the house then? You wouldn\rquote 
