\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 I don\rquote t suppose it was - so elaborate as it is today but we\rquote 
d always a special sort of dinner. Plum pudding. And perhaps one of the fowls were killed. Chicken killed. And we had brussel - brussel sprouts with it, we have that yet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Were the whole family sort of together for Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Oh yes. Yes. But - New Year was always - recognized more in 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Scotland{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} than Christmas Day. Christmas was never the same in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Scotland{\*\xmlclose}
 as it is in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}England{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. It is - becoming - more so now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Can you tell me about New
 Year then, you would be out in the country like that? Would you get first footers and so on?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 
Aye. Well - I - well everybody had a bottle at - at New Year. And - I can remember on New Year\rquote s morning - do you see a - do you see a - a dish in there, a glass dish? Well there\rquote 
s three, I have two of them, and my sister had the - big one, in fact it was her that gave me that one. I - I think it was her that gave me them both. But she had a bigger one still. And on New Year\rquote s morning - that - cake dish was 
filled with - slices of - currant cake, shortbread, and things like that. And the bottle - was put on the table and anyone that come in - got a glass of whisky or a glass of port wine, whatever they wanted, and - a piece of that cake.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Did you have many people coming in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 
Oh - they used to call it first footing. And somebody - would come along at - you were friendly with - and they would be treated to a - a glass of whisky or a glass of port wine, whatever they wanted and - a piece of cake, and - a
nd that was - what you called your New Year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 What about the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Oh well we didn\rquote t - oh we didn\rquote 
t get any whisky or anything like that. Or port wine. No, no, we got cake and shortbread. And we had our orange and our apple.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 You got another orange and apple?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 No, no, that was what we had in our stocking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Was there ever any interest in music in your family, were there any }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13318710\charrsid12015019 musical}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019  instruments in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 A phonograph, I can remem - remember - my brother Willie bringing a p
honograph home, when he come home from his job in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Glasgow{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. And - about a dozen records. And they weren\rquote 
t the records like what we have now, they were round records that you pushed onto a cylinder. And - he brought this and went away and left it and that was the time Harry Lauder - was singing, and we had several of Harry Lauder\rquote 
s songs. And down - on the road to the school - there was a Mary Cameron lived, and she - she adopted a little boy. And - she was asked to come up and - hear the grama - the phonogra
ph. And of course Mary Cameron was talking and - talking away, and wee Willie - shut up Mary, you\rquote ll stop it. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 How old would you be then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 
A wee boy. Oh I would be getting on for twelve. But the wee boy, he - he wasn\rquote t started going to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 He was fascinated by it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 He was fascinated by the - the phonograph.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Did you ever sing in your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Oh we all sung. The whole lot of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Did you sit at night and have a sing song sometimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 On a Sunday night. We\rquote d been 
to church and Sunday school. And when my sister Janet and Nellie - and Richard and I were at home, and my father and my stepmother, we always had a sing song of hymns at night and we all got picking our choice. Our favourite hymn. And we used to sing thes
e hymns at night on a Sunday night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Did you have a piano then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Oh no, we\rquote d no piano. No. We - just sung them together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Did your parents ever play any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Oh we played games at the school. Rounders, and things like that. But
 - I don\rquote t know, after I left school I - I never seemed to have time for games, I\rquote m very fond of watching football, but I never played, I never played football.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Not even at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Oh I daresay I did at school but I - can\rquote t remember much about i
t, but I mean - I didn\rquote t - join any club or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 I was thinking more of like card games and snakes and ladders and things?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 
Oh we had snakes and ladders, my brother and I had snakes and ladders but we never cared much for that game.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Did your mother and father ever play any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 
No, they - they played cards. They used to have a game they played, cath the ten. Well that\rquote s what they played. You see - you cut for trump, and whatever - turns up, hearts or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13318710\charrsid12015019 diamonds}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 , spades or clubs - that\rquote s trump. Now the - the ten of clubs if that\rquote 
s trumps that was the card you\rquote d to try and catch. Aye, well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Were you children allowed to play then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Oh yes, we - we were allowed to play but - we didn\rquote 
t play that so much as - strip Jack naked. That was what we played, Richard and I played that often. Well you deal out the cards. Twenty-six. Aye. Twenty-six-cards each. And }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13318710\charrsid12015019 you\rquote d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 
 start, whoever started threw down a card, if it was a Queen you put three on it. And if you managed to put three plain cards these were yours. But if you - threw two - plain cards - and another face card, you\rquote 
d to stop, the other one had to put - that was - and whoever managed to put the two or three - three I think it was - on the face, they got the cards. And that was what they called strip Jack jaked.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 I\rquote 
ll bet there would be a few arguments with you and your brother then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Oh we used to have our arguments, but they never lasted long.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 How about books in the house, were there many books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 
Oh aye. They - there was plenty of books. But - it was more papers that were read in those days. They used to get the Weekly News and was it Jean McFarland that was in the Weekly News, that - that Jean McFarland was read every week and - and the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Is that a story?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Aye, it was a story. I don\rquote t think it\rquote 
s on now. And - what was the other one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 You said you got the Standard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 
Oh but the Standard Wednesday and Saturday. That was the - Liberal paper, the Courier and Herald was the Tory paper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 There\rquote s no competition nowadays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 No. No, it\rquote s all the Standard, and I think it\rquote 
s more Tory now than -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 
You said that your father read and he liked peace and quiet while he was reading it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Oh yes, he liked peace and quiet when he was reading the Standard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Did you children get a chance to read it as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 
Oh yes, we could read it if we wanted. But - there was another paper used to come in to the house, the Welcome. And there were stories in that that - my father used to read it sometimes to my mother and my mother sometimes read it - read it - to him.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 That\rquote s a woman\rquote s story magazine isn\rquote t it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Well but this - they seemed to be both interested in the stories.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Your father would read it as well? Did they ever read stories to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Oh no. No, no, we\rquote d to read our own stories.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Do you remember any funerals in the family? When you were small?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Do you remember any big funerals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 I can\rquote t remember my mother\rquote s funeral. I was j
ust three years old when she died and I can\rquote t remember the funeral.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 
Can you tell me anything about what funerals were like, from a funeral that happened maybe round about here when you were a wee bit older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 I\rquote ve heard of town funeral
s, I wondered if country funerals were any different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Well I think they\rquote 
re much the same. The people round about, say in a village - everybody knew everybody else, and if anyone died - the majority of the people in the village came to their funeral.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Did they all wear black?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Well, I don\rquote 
t know that they - they always wore black, they just were their Sunday suit. And a bowler hat, a bowler hat in those days. But they\rquote re not so particular nowadays, they go with - some goes bareheaded and some 
- goes with a - a trilby. Very few has the - top hat, the lum hat. Very few goes with the lum hat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Do you remember seeing people with lum hats at funerals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 YES? I can remember, but it was always the gentry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Were they big funerals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 In 
those days - in those days there was three - people in - in the district, there was the Laird, that was - Major Crabbe of Duncow. And there was the minister. And there was the Domini. There were the three main men in - in the district, in those days. And 
I mean if you wanted to - know anything - or wanted to complain about anything, these were the three you had to get in contact with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 They would solve your problems for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Well - in their - in their way. To their satisfaction.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Would you say
 there was any difference between the three of them, was the Laird more important than the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 
Oh the Laird - the Laird seemed to be the most important. And the minister came next I think. And the Domini.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 The Domini was the last resort?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 
Aye, well but I mean he was very - he - he was - well thought of, Mr Sinclair of Duncow, everybody - in fact I have his picture that I cut out of the Standard when he died and that\rquote 
s a long time ago, I came on that picture the other day. That I cut out of the - the Standard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 You started school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 When I was five years old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 And you went to Borwnhall first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 I went to Brownhall school first. And my - teacher was a Miss Kerr.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 It would be quite a small school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Oh it\rquote s not a big school, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 All the different ages were in the one room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 
Well - two - no. There was three rooms. There was the - infants class, and then the second lot, and then there was the master. Mr White was the schoolmaster at Brownhall school in those da
ys. And he lived close beside the school, the school house is just over from the school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Did you have to stay a whole day when you went first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Yes. We went at nine o\rquote 
clock. And we got out at twelve - to one. And we were back in at one - \lquote til four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Were you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13318710\charrsid12015019 able}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019  to go home for your dinner there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 
Oh yes, I was able to go home for my dinner there because I only lived at Wellgreen just a short way across. And at that time - I can remember - my father had got a job helping to unload a boat 
that come into the New Quay, and my stepmother - went away - with his dinner, this day, when I got out at eleven o\rquote clock, and when I came along - here\rquote s my brother Richard - lost looking, where he had been I don\rquote 
t know where - who she had left him with, bu
t he was on his own. And I said, can you find your way home No. I says, well the only thing for it's to take you to school. So I took him to school with me, and Miss Kerr said to him - hold - he was - entertaining all the children - were taken on with him
 you see, being such a young person in school, and they were all talking to him and - and keeping them off their lessons and Miss Kerr says - how old are you Richard? I\rquote m half past four. Well I\rquote m afraid you\rquote 
ll have to stay at home until you\rquote re five o\rquote clock. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13318710\charrsid12015019 It\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019  funny how these things stick in your memory.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 It was just an ordinary board school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Just an ordinary day school. Day school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Like the board schools in the town, run by the school board?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Did you have to go to school on your own, until Richard was old enough?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 How did you like that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 
I liked it all right. In fact I quite enjoyed my schooling days, but I was always looking forward to be - to being fourteen year - a year seemed a terrible lon
g time in these days compared with now. As you get older - as you get older the years seem to go past the quicker. Don\rquote t - have - haven\rquote t you noticed that? Aye, well a - a year at school - seemed a century.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 What was Miss Kerr like, how did you get on with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Oh I got on all right with Miss Kerr, she was - a nice teacher.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Was she strict about anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Oh - she was strict, you weren\rquote 
t allowed to talk or anything like that and this is what annoyed her you know, the other children - being taken on with Richard and - and it - it was keeping them off their lessons. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Was she very fussy about you being tidy and this sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 No, everybody went as tidy as possible to school I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Did she make you speak properly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 She was fussy about that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Oh yes. You werenae allowed to speak Scotch.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Did you speak Scotch outside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Ah, oh aye, it was Scotch all the time you were outside.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Supposing you did something wrong and Miss Kerr wanted to punish you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Oh she didn\rquote t punish us, she shoved you through the door to Mr White.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 You\rquote d to go to the headmaster?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Aye, he did the punishing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 What did you get from him, was it the belt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 No, a cane. It was a cane he had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Would you get the cane on the bottom on your hand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 
Oh on your hands. If you held out your hand and he came down and you did that it was round your legs - next time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 What about the girls, did the girls get the cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Oh they got it
 too. When they needed it. They had more need of it than the boys I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 What sort of things did you get it for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Well - I always remember -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Can you tell me something about Duncow school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
PlaceName}}Duncow{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}School{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 You told me about Brownhall before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Aye. You want to know about Dun -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 What size of school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 
Oh it was - three rooms. Mr Sinclair was the head - teacher. And - I had - three different teachers, while I was there. A Miss Wells. And a Miss Muir. And a Miss Clark.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 So you went through all three classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 
YES. But Mr Sinclair was the head - teacher. And he was there long before me because there was people - well advanced in years had been taught by him, so he\rquote d been there a long time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 What sort of man was he, was he strict?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 
Nice man, no, he was strict but - but I remember - one thing - before I got going to school in the morning I\rquote d - a lot of hens to feed, and some mornings - I had to go down to the - village and get food for them if they ran 
out. And - it was two miles down, it was just beside the school, it was two miles I had to run down to get this food for them and go back and feed the hens and give them water before I went to the school, and very often I was late. And when I went into th
e
 school I had to stand at the door until the schoolteacher, until Mr Sinclair said - come to your seat But one morning he - he was giving them their lesson - and - he said the them - in this - lesson there was the word - wain, and he turns to the class. C
a
n any of you tell the opposite word to - to wane? No answer. And he asked the others in the other classes and still no answer. And I shouted, wax. Oh the boy, the boy, the boy. And he came away up to me and - gave me sixpence, and took me up to my seat. S
ixpence was a lot of money in those days. Now I - how I knew that word we used to - it was one of my favourite hymns, when moon shall wax and wane no more. And that\rquote 
s how I knew. And - that was - one thing that sticks in my memory, getting that sixpence. So -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Was Mr Sinclair very strict about discipline in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Oh - oh yes, oh he was very strict, he hadn\rquote 
t - when he was marking the register he used to put on some and tell who - is talking, and if anybody was talking - they had to come out and they\rquote 
d to stand there until he was ready to deal with them. But I never noticed him being over strict, I mean he was a nice man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 
How about the other boys and girls at this school, were they all much the same sort of people as yourself? Or did you have the better off people there as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 
Oh, no, no, they were all just the same sort of class. A lot of estate workers on Duncow estate. And - some from Kirkton village. And - there was a school at Dalswinton, about half way between Duncow and Dalsw
inton there was a little - village where a lot - people - a lot of the children came from. So they were from all round the district. But there was farmers - farmers sons and daughters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Did the teachers make any difference between farmers daughters and
 estate workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Oh - no, they never made any difference, that I - that I could see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 
How about the children themselves? Did you ever pick on anybody, was there anybody that didn\rquote t belong with the rest of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 You were all quite friendly?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 
We were all - there used to be fights you know, children - used to fall out and have a fight, but I mean it was all over and - done with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Would you ever fight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Can you remember any of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Oh not much, I don\rquote t rem
ember much about fighting. I can - remember being in two fights, but I can\rquote t remember very much about them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Were your parents interested in what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Did they ever go to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Oh no, they never - never went to 
school in these days, the - parents never - never went there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 But they would ask you at home how you were getting on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 
Oh yes, they were interested in how we were getting on at school, of course we used to have lessons to do at home. And they always saw to it - that they were done before we got out to - play or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 How long did you stay at Duncow School?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 I think I would be six years at Duncow school altogether.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 You would leave when you were fourteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 No. No, I
 - I left when I - I left there when I was nineteen because I spent the last year of my schooling at Holywood school with a Mr Kennedy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 When you were how old?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 
Thirteen I should think when - when I was thirteen and - and - I left school when I was fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 You didn\rquote t go to a secondary school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Oh no. No, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 
Do you have any regrets about your education, or were you quite happy to leave?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Oh I was quite happy to leave, I mean - everybody wanted to leave - we didn
\rquote t realize then that they were the best days of our life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 You think so now on looking back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 
Oh yes. I think these were really the happiest days of your life when you were at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 What did you do in the days when you were at school, how about playing?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Playing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Did you have much time to go out and play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 
Oh we got an hour for our dinner. And - but I had to go home for my dinner. Not while we were at Ellerslie, it was two miles to go and I hadn\rquote t time to go there but when we lived at Lakes
ide it was less than a mile and I had to go home for my dinner then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 So you didn\rquote t have so much time to play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Who did you play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 
Well we used to play games - when was they called it rounders. And - you remember rounders. There was one put in that corner and one in that corner and one in this corner and - this corner here. And - I just can\rquote 
t remember how it was - played but it was like two sides, there was one batting and - someone threw a ball, and this one - batted the ball aw
ay, and - you run from corner to corner you see. You still play that? Ah well, that was - that was the game that we played, usually, and football if we could get an old tennis ball or anything like that to play football with, we used to play at football. 
We never had a real football.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 
How about when you were at home though, away from the school? Who did you have to play with then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 At home? Oh I\rquote 
d only my brother to play with there because I had to work. I - I had all these hens to feed that I\rquote ve told you about. And - on the Saturdays I had to clean out all the hen houses, there was six of them altogether. So - I didn\rquote 
t get much time for playing. But I used to get fishing. That was what amused me more than anything. There was a - a lake ran past the house. And - we hadn\rquote t fishing rods, we\rquote 
d only a - a - a willow wand with a - penny line and a - a penny bait hook tied on the end of it. But it worked. We - I used to catch - catch odd trouts with it but it was mostly eels and we had a tub - that we used to put these eels in of - I\rquote 
ve - I\rquote ve seen us having as many as a dozen eels in that - but my father used to always make us empty them out and they just crawled through the grass and into the water at night. But - at this place - my brother Richard was th
ree years younger than I was, and we were fishing this day, and we were standing on a step, there was a step down where you could go down and get a bucket full of water or wash pots or anything like that. And we were standing on this - it was about that l
ong and about that broad. We were both standing fishing for eels on this - and I thought I would put on a new - a new bait, and I\rquote 
d just jumped off the step onto the bank to put this - and the step - overbalanced with me getting off it and he - he went in o
ver the head. So I threw down my line and I run in after him and pulled him out. And I took him - up home and as we were going up home he says, Bob, will they put me through the mangle? That was Richie. There\rquote s his photograph there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 How about when yo
u were playing, did you get into trouble if you got dirty, or did Richard get into trouble when he got soaked that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Oh no, not much trouble, they were pleased that he didn\rquote t get downed.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 What sort of places did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Well we\rquote d any a room there, we\rquote d - we\rquote 
d a big orchard. And - my father used to - rear turkeys, and hens, and - of course I had to look after them because he was away at his work, especially in the wintertime when the days were short. He - he was - he was only at home in
 the - on the Sundays really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 So it was your responsibility?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 So it was my responsibility to look after these - hens.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Did you ever go for walks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 
Huh, I never had time to go for walks much unless it was on the Sunday. I daresay we went for walks on the Sunday occasionally. But we had to go to Sunday }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13318710\charrsid12015019 
school}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019  - we had to go to Sunday school in the morning and then - we\rquote 
d to - when we come out of the Sunday school - our parents met us and went to church, we all went to church. To go - they went to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Did you go for a walk in the afternoon with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 
Sometimes. Sometimes. But - I mean everybody went to church in those days, not - it\rquote s - it\rquote s different from today, there\rquote s hardly anybody - there\rquote s very few goes to church today compared with what they did in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 So everybody would go?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 
Aye, everybody did go. Everybody. We used to see them going past - from - all from Duncow right down to Kirkton, that was about two miles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 How about the church through the w
eek, did the church have much influence in the peoples lives through the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 No, just - church - I don\rquote t think the church - I can\rquote 
t remember the church ever being opened except for weddings or - or - or - or - service - services at funerals or anything like that, that was about anything that - I remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 They didn\rquote t have women\rquote s guilds and things like they have now?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 No, I can\rquote t remember anything like that anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 You didn\rquote t go to anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 No. I never went to anythin
g like that, we used to have a Sunday school treat at Christmas time, that was about all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Did you have a party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Oh yes. Couldn\rquote 
t call it a party but we used to get a - bag of - buns and an orange and an apple. But that was about all that children did get in those days, they didn\rquote t get as much as they get today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 There wasn\rquote t the money then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 No, that\rquote s right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 How about a Sunday school trip, did you have something in the summer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Yes, we used to have a Sunday school trip once a 
year, and it was just some of the farmers fetched their carts and - collected us and - took us away, oh - six or eight miles away somewhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 It would seem quite a long way when you were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 It - it - pleased us anyway, of course there was no 
- motor coaches or anything like that, that\rquote s a thing since the - since the first world war really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 What did you do on your trip?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 
Well, we used to have sports, running and - different things, for to - and got prizes for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 You had a good time there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Oh, had - quite a nice time. Pleased the children anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Were you ever in the choir at the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 No. I never - I don\rquote 
t think there was a church childrens choir at that church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 How about any temperance clubs, anything like that? Like the Band of Hope?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 No, I - I - I never - I never belonged to it anyway, if there, I don\rquote 
t remember any Band of Hope. There was the Boys Brigade, but I - I wasn\rquote t a member of that either.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 You could have been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Oh I could have been if I\rquote d wanted to join I daresay.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 You just didn\rquote t fancy it then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Oh I don\rquote t know. I - I had plenty to do at home I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Would you say that your parents were quite religious people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Quite religious? Oh - most people were religiou
s in those days, I mean - they all went to church anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 How about at home, did you say grace when you were having a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 
Yes. And - on a Sunday evening, when - when my sisters were at home, we used to have - a night - every Sunday night we used to sing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13318710\charrsid12015019 
 hymns and - we picked the one t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 hat - we liked bed, each one had their turn at picking the hymn that they wanted to sing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Were you taught to say your prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 YES. OH yes. I think the most of the children said their prayers in
 those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Did you ever have prayers altogether, family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 
Only on that Sunday night, on the Sunday nights after the - singing of the hymns. Fin - my father finished off - saying a prayer, or reading a piece of the Bible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 You said your father was interested in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 
Oh yes. He did - he - he - in fact - Dumfriesshire was a strong Liberal constituency in those days. The majority of them - in Dumfriesshire were Liberals. And it\rquote s just - since we\rquote ve come down into this district that they\rquote 
ve turned Tory. The member - the Liberal Member, or the Liberal Candidate - came up and called himself a Liberal Conservative, if you ever heard tell of a Liberal Conservative you\rquote re - I think you\rquote 
re either a Liberal with the welfare of your fellow men at heart throughout the world or you - you\rquote re a Conservative who never did anything in his life but bleed his fellow men to death to safeguard his own selfish interest. That\rquote 
s my definition of a Liberal.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 You think you can\rquote t be halfway in between?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 I don\rquote 
t think so. And he came up and called himself a Liberal Conservative, and he got in, and immediately he got in he said, I\rquote m really a Conservative. And they made him a Lord.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 How about your father\rquote s views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Was he a member of the Liberal party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 He - he - well I don\rquote 
t know about him being a member of the Liberal party but he was a very strong - Liberal. And he walked to his work four miles, he had to be away at ten minutes to six in the morning to be at his work at 
seven, to start as seven. And he worked to six at night and walked the four miles home, and while he was sitting at his supper a Mr Armstrong that was in a smallholding nearby come in dressed and he said, Davy, are you no going to vote? And father, says, 
wait \lquote til I get my supper and, he says, I\rquote ll come with you. And they walked the seven miles into {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Dumfries{\*\xmlclose}
 and the seven miles back to give their vote for the - the candidate was - Mr Malteno. But that\rquote s a good while - good few years ago. And he got in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 
Did you find your father was on the estate there, did the owners the estate try and influence the workers at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 
Oh they did. But - the - the funny thing about that place - Captain Campbell Johnson was never at home, I expect he would be a Tory, but he was - he never seemed to be there, whether he was away in the army or where he was I don\rquote 
t know. But - my father worked on the estate, he and another man. And - I can\rquote t ever remember seeing Captain Campbell Johnson. So whether he was away in the army - being a Captain he would be likely. But I didn\rquote t - I couldn\rquote 
t tell you where he was. But he - he never seemed to be there. But - I know the majority of - of these estate people were Tories. And they were awful kind to the - voters while the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13318710\charrsid12015019 election}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019  was 
on, bringing them pairs of rabbits and such like. As much as to say this is for you to vote for me. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 
Did it ever work the other way round, did they ever turn round and say if you don\rquote t vote Conservative?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3887919 RS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Oh I never knew them doing that. No,
 no. But - I daresay it happened. I daresay that happened if they found out that you were voting - for anyone else, that didn\rquote t happen on - my - in my father\rquote s case. Because I\rquote m sure he didn\rquote t - he didn\rquote 
t conceal it in any way that he was a Liberal.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9711576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9980725\charrsid12015019 Did he do anything about politics in between elections?
