s a - a horsedrawn bus used to go twice a week to Dumfries and she used to to go for messages. And - but she never was one to go - visiting in other peoples houses, I c
ould almost tell you all the times I knew her being in any peoples houses and it was at New Year. My father after he finished his work one New Year I remember - he had gone in - to the - the other forester\rquote 
s house. And she got worried, wondered - what was keeping him, and she went off. To see - what had happened to him. And here - she stayed on to to enjoy herself. And there was just my sister Nellie - and Richard and I at home. So she didn\rquote 
