 home together I remember this all my days. My sister Nellie - was asleep like this in front of the fire. Sound asleep. Because Richard was sent too, she sent Richard to see and - we met Richard coming on our
 way home. And when we come home that was Nellie was lying - on her knees sleeping at the fire. It was into the morning. It was either - I can\rquote 
